Message.MsgText: OCSP_JMS_DestAlreadyMember=OCSP0007I: Destination {0} is already part of default work class {1} in application {2}.
Message.Explanation: Work class membership of destination will not changed.
Message.UserResponse: For optimal results, a given destination cannot be consumed by more than one module.

Message.MsgText: OCSP_JMS_NoDestDefinedModule=OCSP0005I: No matching destination defined in cell for resource reference binding {0} defined by module {1}
Message.Explanation: Unable to map jms resource jndi binding to destination in the current cell.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure destination and bus name defined by the resource exist in the current cell.

Message.MsgText: OCSP_NodeIn2Grps=OCSP0001E: Node {0} is in two node groups, {1} and {2}, and will therefore not be used.
Message.Explanation: A node was detected to be a member of multiple node groups and will therefore not be used until the condition is resolved.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure each node is a member of at most one node group and restart all processes.

Message.MsgText: OCSP_JMS_NoDestDefined=OCSP0004I: No matching destination defined in cell for resource reference binding {0} with destination {1} and Bus {2}
Message.Explanation: Unable to map jms resource jndi binding to destination in the current cell.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure destination and bus name defined by the resource exist in the current cell.

Message.MsgText: OCSP_UnknownNode=OCSP0003E: Node {0} was not found. Invalid custom property value of ''node.name'' in endpoint of generic server cluster {1}.
Message.Explanation: The ''node.name'' custom property of a generic server cluster endpoint refers to a non-existent node.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the node which is specified by the ''node.name'' property exists.

Message.MsgText: OCSP_JMS_DESTSWITCH=OCSP0006I: Destination {0} is being updated to be part of work class {1} in application {2}. Earlier it was part of default workclass of {3}
Message.Explanation: Work class membership of destination changed.
